  <facilityDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Restaurants &amp; Bars</span></strong></p>
<p>With its peaked ceiling and beach-washed colours, the elegant yet comfortable restaurant at Hotel Acacia Marina offers typical Sicilian cuisine in a relaxed setting. It offers a rich and varied buffet for breakfast and dinner. </p>
<p>For those wanting to try something different, the a la carte restaurant at Acacia Marina offers a more extensive menu of Italian cuisine from around the country and can be booked and paid for locally.</p>
<p>After dinner, we suggest taking a nightcap or coffee at the hotel lobby bar which you can enjoy out on the terrace as the sun sets behind the dazzling waters of the Mediterranean.</p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Pools &amp; Beaches </span></strong></p>
<p>Surrounded by tropical gardens, the 400m² pool at Hotel Acacia Marina is the ideal spot to kick back and relax in the Sicilian sunshine. With plenty of sun loungers and umbrellas and an additional outdoor hot tub, this is perfect for those days when you want to completely escape the world and take some time for yourself.</p>
<p>Alternatively, you can take a stroll to the gorgeous blue flag certified beach just 100 yards from the hotel. Here you'll find golden sands sloping into the glittering waters of the Mediterranean sea. A beach service with sun loungers and parasols for hire (payable locally) is available from 01 Jun - 30 Sep (weather dependent). </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Spa</span></strong></p>
<p>The quaint but stylish spa located within the main building offers use of a sauna, whirlpool, fitness room and treatments room where you can enjoy massages, beauty therapies and aroma treatments. *Please note that the sauna and treatments require payment locally.</p>]]></facilityDescription>
